node.text:
Invisible Wounds: Recovery and Resilience
.
Everyone is susceptible to invisible wounds. Being able to recognize one of these wounds, and using positive language when discussing it, supports a positive culture across the Department of the Air Force and could save a life. It is important for Airmen and Guardians to seek help for invisible wounds, taking that first step towards recovery.
.
This video describes the importance of Airmen and Guardians seeking help for invisible wounds and how taking that first step towards recovery results in positive outcomes and enhanced resilience.
.
#InvisibleWounds #MentalHealthAwarenessMonth

node.text:
Invisible Wounds: Risk, Impact, and Available Resources
.
Over the past five years, United States Department of the Air Force’s Invisible Wounds Initiative has implemented solutions that drive timely, proactive case handling, equitable, informed interactions and decisions, engaged leadership and a supportive environment, and accessible, effective care delivery. 
.
Everyone is susceptible to invisible wounds. The impact of invisible wounds and can develop at any time, in any place, in or out of uniform.
.
Learn more at: https://go.usa.gov/xszpN
.
#InvisibleWounds #MentalHealthAwarenessMonth

node.title: Invisible Wounds: Risk, Impact, and Available Resources

node.text:
Invisible Wounds: Signs and Symptoms
.
Since its inception in 2016, the United States Department of the Air Force’s Invisible Wounds Initiative has been a leader in creating a supportive culture for #Airmen living with invisible wounds. Being able to recognize an invisible wound could save a life. Airman can learn to see the signs and symptoms of invisible wounds in others that they may see in themselves.
.
#InvisibleWounds #MentalHealthAwarenessMonth

node.text:
Air Force Chief of Staff Gen. Charles Q. Brown, Jr., & @cmsaf_official discuss how empowering Airmen will lead to success in building the future Air Force today. They also discussed Accelerate Change or Lose, the Action Orders, leadership and followership, how to rise above bias & self-limitations, and the future of the #AirForce.
.
The primary focus of this call was to connect with Airmen across the world, and give insight to how the Action orders, new Air Force missions statement and developmental guidance are being implemented for the Total Force.
.
#RealTalk #CoffeeTalk #Future #Empowerment #Questions

Homecoming
.
An Airman from the 389th Fighter Squadron hugs his daughter after returning to @mhafb_gunfighters, Idaho from an eight month deployment.

.
📸 by A1C Andrew Kobialka
.
#deployment #militaryphotography #USAF

node.text:
Give me liberty or--
.
The 493rd Fighter Squadron operates out of RAF Leeming, United Kingdom, during Agile Liberty 21-2. The @48fighterwing regularly conducts joint exercises with UK forces in order to demonstrate and improve interoperability and Agile Combat Employment capabilities which include using new technologies to increase their effectiveness.
.
🎥 by SrA John Ennis
.
#aircraft #USAF #militaryforces #liberty

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by U.S. Air Force on September 01, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and body of water.

node.text:
Come on in, the water's fine 👍
.
Capt. Trent Vonich, 38th Rescue Squadron pararescueman and Blue Team flight commander, poses for a photo after conducting water jumps into the Banana River near Patrick Space Force Base, Florida. 
.
Designed to prepare pararescuemen for supporting the SpaceX human spaceflight program and Boeing’s spaceflight program, training is crucial to rescue operations due to the high level of teamwork required and the physically demanding scenarios pararescuemen encounter. 
.
📸 by SSgt Devin Boyer
.
@spaceforcedod #spaceX

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by U.S. Air Force on August 31, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and outdoors.

node.text:
Don't forget to hydrate 💧 
.
Staff Sgt. Andrew Stefanic, 435th Contingency Response Squadron cyber transport systems technician, takes a sip of water while helping measure the perimeter of a logistics support area during Thracian Summer 2021 at Cheshnegirovo drop zone, Bulgaria. The logistics support area establishes a space where U.S. military members can reside and conduct operations for the duration of the exercise. 
.
📸 by SrA Andrew J. Alvarado
.
#militaryphotography #NATO #USAF

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by U.S. Air Force on August 31, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, military uniform and outdoors.

node.text:
Honor & remember today and every day after
.
Members of the Defense POW/MIA Accounting Agency (DPAA) render salutes during a disinterment ceremony at the National Memorial Cemetery of the Pacific in Honolulu, Hawaii. 
.
The ceremony was part of the agency’s efforts to disinter and identify the remains of unknown service members lost during the Korean War. DPAA’s mission is to achieve the fullest possible accounting for missing and unaccounted-for U.S. personnel to their families and our nation. 
.
📸 by SSgt Jonathan McElderry
.
#militaryphotography #silhouettephotography #nationalmemorialcemetery

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by U.S. Air Force on August 31, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and military uniform.

node.text:
Fueling the fleet
.
Airmen with a @usafcent expeditionary logistics readiness squadron recently worked to pump 1,000,000 gallons of fuel in a single day to support evacuation operations. That's enough fuel to fill a pool nearly as large as a football field! 
.
📸 by A1C Kylie Barrow
.
#currentevents #militaryphotography

@airforcespecialtactics operators breach a door during close-quarters battle training at exercise Southern Strike. 
.
Special Tactics teams are trained to shoot, move and communicate while bringing airpower expertise to the ground force. 
.
#SOF #AFSPECWAR #USAF #specialtactics

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by U.S. Air Force on August 29, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and standing.

node.text:
Taking pride in the work you do >>>
.
Airman 1st Class Aaron Edwards, 18th Aircraft Maintenance Unit crew chief at @eielsonafb, Alaska, fills a vital role to make sure to ensure his team's aircraft remain at the top of their game. 
.
Crew chiefs are skilled maintenance professionals with a responsibility for overseeing daily maintenance, identifying malfunctions and replacing parts, conducting inspections and maintaining records, and coordinating aircraft care.
.
#aircraft #maintenance #USAF

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by U.S. Air Force on August 29, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and outdoors.

node.text:
Airmen provide security during exercise Patriot Warrior at Fort McCoy, Wisconsin. The defenders secure the perimeter and check for threats in order to protect base personnel. 
.
Patriot Warrior, one of the @USAFreserve Command’s largest field training exercises, simulates a combat environment to provide Citizen Airmen experience working in deployed conditions. 
.
 📸 by SSgt Shelton Sherrill
.
#USAF #militaryphotography #militarypolice

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by U.S. Air Force on August 28, 2021. May be an image of nature and body of water.

node.text:
Air & sea working in tandem

This is another example of strategic deterrence, showcasing how the joint force links capabilities together for national defense.
.
#aircraft #submarine #nuclear #militaryphotography
